Installation and Configuration of Virtual Environment and Flask Library

1) create a folder called flasktutorial
2) open folder flasktutorial inside vscode
3) go to terminal and run command "python -m venv virtual"
4) can see virtual folder created
5) cd virtual/scripts
6) Type "activate"
7)you can see (virtual) current working folder path
8) let us install flask libraries inside virtual environment
9) cd ../..
10) now you inside flasktutorial
11) type "pip install flask"
12) install all necessary libraries
13) come out of virtual, cd virtual/scripts
14) type "deactivate"

Developing web application using Flask
1) create a python program called app.py
2) in terminal, make sure you are inside folder where app.py is
